A 12 year old knows it is wrong to kill someone<br>
A 12 year old knows that it is wrong to touch someone sexually without thier consent<br>
A 12 year old knows it wrong to use drugs<br>
A 12 year old knows its wrong to steal<br>
<br>
If the 12 year old isnt mentally challenged, and doesnt know these things, then the PARENT is WRONG.<br>
<br>
Since a twelve year old is old enough to understand right from wrong, everyone above that age should know it as well. Since we all know right from wrong, we should be punished for doing wrong. <br>
<br>
Here is my train of thought:<br>
18 yrs old - Old enough to move out on his/her own and make their own descisions. Must have knowledge and skills to succeed and survive.<br>
16 yrs old - 2 years until they are on their own. They need to have the knowledge and skills to succeed and survive and refine them over the following 2 years.<br>
14 yrs old - Childhood is over, time to start learning the skills needed to survive on thier own, high school is starting and they need to start acting like yound adults.<br>
12 yrs old - time to start taking responsibility for thier actions, need to know right from wrong, how to take care of themselves, and how to behave appropriately for the situation<br>
